MIDDLESBROUGH. Pep Guardiola insists he is keeping all his options open as he pursues a trophy in his first season at Manchester City.Guardiola s side are still in contention in the English Premier League and Champions League soccer, but the City manager appears equally committed to success in the FA Cup. Facing a quarter-final at Premier League strugglers Middlesbrough on Saturday, Guardiola admirably resisted the temptation to rest several of his most influential players with a Champions League trip to Monaco only four days away.The Spaniard was rewarded with a 2-0 victory that represented the ideal preparation for Wednesday s game where they lead 5-3 after the last 16 first leg, and a daunting run of English Premier League fixtures against Liverpool, Arsenal and Chelsea. AFP&nbsp;